<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Observer: Spoken for
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Iron Lady is still stealing the show over Europe, as witness her
performance at the International Securities Market Association's conference
in Munich.
Appearing alongside German finance minister Theo Waigel, Mrs Thatcher
advanced the thesis that all EC convergence means is other countries getting
bigger subsidies from Germany and Britain. Isn't that right, she asked,
turning to Waigel for support - only to find he had slipped away.
'Well,' she said, unperturbed. 'If he were still here, he'd say yes.'
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
